    <section class="about-content">
        <div class="about-grid">
            <div>
                <h2>Our Story</h2>
                <p>For more than 25 years, Diana Rose has worked closely with private families in childcare and household support. Over that time, she has learned that the right person in a family home is never only about skills. It is about trust, responsibility, warmth, respect, and the ability to care for a household with professionalism and discretion.</p>
                <p>Through years of working with children, parents, and household teams, Diana has built long-standing relationships with families and experienced professionals. Many of the people she recommends are known through her own trusted network — people she has worked with, trained, supported, or come to know through reliable family connections.</p>
                <p>This personal approach is at the heart of Trusted Household &amp; Childcare. We do not present families with a public database of unknown profiles. We first take time to understand the family&rsquo;s needs, expectations, household culture, and the kind of person who would truly fit. Only then do we suggest suitable candidates privately.</p>
                <p>Diana created this service because she saw how difficult it can be for families to find someone they can genuinely trust. A good nanny, housekeeper, chef, or household professional becomes part of the rhythm of the home. The right match brings calm, confidence, and peace of mind.</p>
                <p>Our focus is simple: responsible people, caring work, respectful introductions, and long-term trust.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2>Our Approach</h2>
                <p>Every introduction begins with a private consultation. We listen first: your family structure, schedule, children&rsquo;s needs, household standards, language preferences, and the type of support that would make daily life easier.</p>
                <p>From there, we introduce suitable professionals privately and carefully. Candidate details, CVs, and references are not shared publicly. They are discussed only after consultation, when we understand what your household truly needs.</p>
                <p>Our network is built through personal relationships, practical experience, and trusted recommendations. We look for people who are responsible, respectful, caring, and able to work with families in a professional manner.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

